{"title_page": "Sfera Ebbasta", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sfera Ebbasta \n| image              = Sfera Ebbasta (cropped 2).jpg\n| image_size         = 200\n| caption            = Sfera Ebbasta in 2016\n| birth_name         = Gionata Boschetti e Alberelli\n| alias              = {{flatlist|\n*Sfera\n}}\n| partner            = Tua Madre\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1992|12|7|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Sesto San Giovanni]], [[Lombardy]], [[Italy]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background         = solo_singer<!--mandatory field-->\n| Genre              = {{flatlist|\n* [[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]\n* [[Pop rap]]\n* [[Latin trap]]\n\n}}\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Disoccupato\n}}\n| years_active       = 2011\u20132020\n| label              = {{flatlist|\n* BillionHeadz Music Group|BillionHeadz\n* [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n* [[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n}}\n| associated_acts    = {{flatlist|\n* [[Charlie Charles]]\n* [[Ghali (rapper)|Ghali]]\n* [[Tedua]]\n* [[Gu\u00e9 Pequeno]]\n* Drefgold\n* [[Quavo]]\n* [[Rich the Kid]]\n* [[Lacrim]]\n* [[Tinie Tempah]]\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|sferaebbasta.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Gionata Boschetti'''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mondorap.it/leta-e-i-veri-nomi-dei-rapper-e-beatmaker-italiani/|title=L'et\u00e0 e i veri nomi dei rapper e beatmaker italiani - Mondo Rap|date=23 December 2015|work=Mondo Rap|access-date=22 June 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref> ({{IPA-it|\u02c8\u02a4onata bo\u02c8sketti}}; born 7 December 1992 in [[Sesto San Giovanni]], [[Lombardy]]), better known by the pseudonym '''Sfera Ebbasta''' ({{IPA-it|\u02c8sf\u025b\u02d0ra eb\u02c8basta|pron}}), is an Italian rapper.\n\nSfera Ebbasta rose to prominence after the release of the ''XDVR'' album, recorded with the collaboration of the [[record producer]] [[Charlie Charles]], which achieved commercial success in Italy. This success was replicated with releases ''Sfera Ebbasta'' (2016), ''[[Rockstar (Sfera Ebbasta album)|Rockstar]]'' (2018), and its re-issue ''Popstar Edition'' (2018).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/news-musica/sfera-ebbasta-e-il-primo-italiano-nella-top-100-di-spotify/399639/|title=Che vi piaccia o meno, Sfera Ebbasta \u00e8 il primo italiano nella Top 100 di Spotify|last=Italia|first=Rolling Stone|work=Rolling Stone Italia|access-date=22 June 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\n\n===First years (2011\u20132013)===\nSfera was born in the [[Milan]]ese town of [[Sesto San Giovanni]], but grew up in the neighbourly [[Cinisello Balsamo]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/music/storie-music/2018/03/30/sfera-ebbasta-trap-canzoni-intervista-foto-concerti-tour|author=Lorenza Sebasiani|title=Sfera Ebbasta: \"Sono il nuovo ragazzo della Via Gluck\"|language=it|work=Vanity Fair|date=30 March 2018|accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref> where the rapper began his musical activity by uploading videos on [[YouTube]] between 2010 and 2012 without any success.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/interviste-musica/sfera-acab-intervista/313754/#Part4|title=Un bravo ragazzo in un brutto quartiere: intervista a Sfera Ebbasta|last=Italia|first=Rolling Stone|work=Rolling Stone Italia|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> In this period he started getting into contact with producer Charlie Charles, during a [[Hip Hop TV]] party.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/it/article/rdpwnv/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-intervista|title=Loro di Sfera Ebbasta non sanno niente|date=2015-06-10|work=Noisey|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it}}</ref> Thus, they formed the [[Crew|collective]] ''Billion Headz Money Gang'', better known by the acronym BHMG. On 15 September 2013, he published ''Emergenza Mixtape Vol. 1''.\n\n===''XDVR'' (2014-2016)===\nSince November 2014, he has produced several pieces in collaboration with Charlie Charles and published them on YouTube with their videos. After the release of the song ''Panette'' he began to be contacted by some record labels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.panorama.it/musica/intervista-sfera-ebbasta-tour-date-album/|title=Intervista a Sfera Ebbasta: \"Il mio tour al via: da Ciny fino a... Hollywood Blvd\" - Panorama|last=Politan\u00f2|first=Matteo|date=2016-10-13|work=Panorama|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 June 2015 he made his debut with the first studio album ''XDVR'' (standing for \"per davvero\", in English \"for real\"), made up by some of the singles published in the previous months, as well as other unpublished ones. Initially released as a free download,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicattitude.it/attualita/news/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-nuovo-album-xdvr/116978|title=Sfera Ebbasta & Charlie Charles, il nuovo album \"XDVR\" in free download - Music Attitude - Tutta la Musica di cui hai davvero bisogno|website=www.musicattitude.it|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> the album was reissued in a reloaded version on November 23 through ''Roccia Music'', an [[independent record label]] of [[Marracash]] and Shablo, and distributed in the national sales circuits; in addition to the songs already present in the original, the tracklist included the unreleased ''XDVRMX'' (with Marracash and Luch\u00e8), ''Ciny'' (referring to his hometown Cinisello, of which video clip was also shot)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.webl0g.net/2015/11/25/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-il-video-di-xdvrmx-con-marracash-e-luche-oltre-50mila-views-in-un-giorno/|title=Sfera Ebbasta & Charlie Charles: il video di XDVRMX con Marracash e Luche. Oltre 50mila views in un giorno {{!}} Musica e Tv 2.0|date=2015-11-25|work=Musica e Tv 2.0|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> and ''Trap Kings''. The album received a good success in the underground musical scene and greatly increased the popularity of [[trap music]] in Italy, also receiving excellent feedback from the specialized critics;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161127022856/http://www.barrediplutonio.com/2015/06/05/xdvr-non-e-solo-un-disco-ma-una-mentalita/|title=\"XDVR\" non \u00e8 solo un disco, ma una mentalit\u00e0! - Barre Di Plutonio|date=2016-11-27|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> however it was also the subject of numerous criticisms as various songs spoke of life in [[suburb]]an neighborhoods (mainly inspired by the street reality of his city, Cinisello Balsamo),<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ilgiorno.it/spettacoli/musica/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-1.1213162|title=Sfera Ebbasta e Charlie Charles, la musica (t)rap che conquista Marracash arriva dai \"quartieri\" - Il Giorno|last=Giorno|first=Il|date=2015-08-12|work=Il Giorno|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> including criminal activities and consumption of [[drug]]s such as [[codeine]] and [[marijuana]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.rockit.it/news/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-nuova-etichetta|title=Sfera Ebbasta e Charlie Charles hanno fondato una loro etichetta|work=Rockit.it|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 January 2016 the video of the unreleased track ''Blunt & Sprite'' was published on YouTube,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.honiro.it/novita_videoclip-blunt-sprite-per-sfera-ebbasta-e-charlie-charles.html|title=Videoclip {{!}} 'Blunt & Sprite' per Sfera Ebbasta e Charlie Charles {{!}} News Honiro|website=www.honiro.it|language=it|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> while during the same year Sfera Ebbasta featured in a track of the album ''Anarchie'' by the French rapper [[SCH (rapper)|SCH]], positively impressed by listening to the rapper's pieces during a stay in Italy: he also made the track ''Cartine'' ''Cartier'', produced by Charlie Charles and DJ Kore, extracted as a promotional [[Single (music)|single]] of the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rapburger.com/2016/05/25/sch-e-sfera-ebbasta-presentano-il-singolo-cartine-cartier/|title=SCH e Sfera Ebbasta presentano il singolo \"Cartine Cartier\"|website=www.rapburger.com|language=it-IT|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref>\n\n===''Sfera Ebbasta'' (2016\u20132017)===\nOn 9 September 2016 the rapper published his first solo studio [[album]], the homonymous ''Sfera Ebbasta'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rockit.it/news/sfera-ebbasta-charlie-charles-album-def-jam-universal|title=Sfera Ebbasta firma per Def Jam e Universal|work=Rockit.it|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> distributed by the record Universal (in collaboration with [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]) and anticipated by the singles ''BRNBQ'' (which received a golden record certificate for over 25,000 copies sold),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:tutte/year:0/page:0/term:BRNBQ|title=FIMI - Certificazioni - FIMI|website=www.fimi.it|language=it|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> ''Cartine Cartier'' and ''Figli di pap\u00e0'', the latter a platinum-certified record for having sold over 50,000 copies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fimi.it/certificazioni#/category:tutte/year:0/page:0/term:Figli_di_papa|title=FIMI - Certificazioni - FIMI|website=www.fimi.it|language=it|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> In this album the rapper detached himself from the more [[Gangsta rap|gangsta]] themes of ''XDVR'' to open himself to wider topics.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/spettacolo/sfera-ebbasta-esce-il-primo-album-ufficiale-abbiamo-cambiato-la-scena-rap-italiana-_3030314-201602a.shtml|title=Sfera Ebbasta, esce il primo album ufficiale: \"Abbiamo cambiato la scena rap italiana...\" - Tgcom24|work=Tgcom24|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> Supported by a promotion also at a television level, participating in broadcasts such as ''Matrix Chiambretti'' on Canale 5<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mondorap.it/sfera-ebbasta-ospite-chiambretti-canale-5-video-completo/|title=Sfera Ebbasta ospite da Chiambretti su canale 5 (video completo) - Mondo Rap|date=2016-11-26|work=Mondo Rap|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> and the radio program ''Albertino Everyday'', conducted by Albertino on [[Radio DeeJay|Radio Deejay]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.deejay.it/news/sfera-ebbasta-dalla-dura-realta-di-cinisello-ai-microfoni-di-albertino-everyday/494344/|title=Sfera Ebbasta: dalla dura realt\u00e0 di Cinisello ai microfoni di Albertino Everyday {{!}} Radio Deejay|date=2016-09-08|work=Radio Deejay|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> the album received great success in Italy, debuting at the top of the album charts, as well as entering the charts of various [[Europe]]an countries;<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2016/09/27/spettacoli/quel-bravo-ragazzo-di-periferia-al-numero-uno-in-classifica-M5cUh8tCtqoSvWQE27iLjI/pagina.html|title=Sfera Ebbasta, quel bravo ragazzo di periferia al numero uno in classifica|work=LaStampa.it|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> the album was also certified as a gold record by [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]] for having sold over 25,000 copies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rapburger.com/2017/01/16/sfera-ebbasta-e-disco-doro-e-figli-di-papa-e-disco-di-platino/|title=Sfera Ebbasta \u00e8 Disco D'Oro e Figli di Pap\u00e0 \u00e8 Disco Di Platino|website=www.rapburger.com|language=it-IT|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> Between October 2016 and March 2017, the rapper promoted the album through the ''Sfera Ebbasta Tour,'' performing in various cities of Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ilgiorno.it/milano/spettacoli/sfera-ebbasta-1.2573165|title=Parte \"Sfera Ebbasta tour\": ecco tutte le date dei concerti - Il Giorno|last=FRA.NE.|date=2016-10-07|work=Il Giorno|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\n===''Rockstar'' (2017\u2013present)===\nOn 10 March 2017, Sfera Ebbasta released the single ''Dexter'', produced by Charlie Charles and Sick Luke,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.panorama.it/musica/sfera-ebbasta-dexter-nuovo-singolo-video-testo/|title=\u00c8 uscito \"Dexter\", il nuovo singolo di Sfera Ebbasta - Panorama|last=Politan\u00f2|first=Matteo|date=2017-03-10|work=Panorama|access-date=2018-06-22|language=it-IT}}</ref> as well as taking part in Charlie Charles's single ''Bimbi'' along with rappers Izi, Rkomi, [[Tedua]] and [[Ghali (rapper)|Ghali]]. Subsequently, the rapper performed at the TIM MTV Awards 2017 and at the [[Wind Music Awards|Wind Music Awards 2017]], during which he presented a further unreleased song, ''Tran Tran'', published on June 9 for digital download.\n\nOn September 22 of the same year [[Gu\u00e8 Pequeno|Gu\u00e9 Pequeno]] released the single ''Lamborghini'' in his album entitled ''Gentleman,'' which featured the vocal participation of Sfera Ebbasta;<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.mtv.it/musica/elettra-lamborghini-nuovo-video-gue-pequeno/|title=Elettra Lamborghini SUPER nel nuovo video di Gu\u00e8 Pequeno e Sfera Ebbasta|date=2017-09-26|work=News Mtv Italia|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> this single achieved good success in Italy, reaching the peak of Top Singoli, the official ranking for the most listened and sold singles in Italy.\n\nOn 3 January 2018 the rapper announced his third studio album ''[[Rockstar (Sfera Ebbasta album)|Rockstar]]'', produced again by Charlie Charles and released on the 19th of the same month.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.mtv.it/musica/sfera-ebbasta-rockstar-il-nuovo-album-2018-uscita-il-19-gennaio/|title=Sfera Ebbasta, \"Rockstar\": il nuovo album in uscita il 19 gennaio - News Mtv Italia|date=2018-01-03|work=News Mtv Italia|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> The album was commercialized in Italian and international editions, the latter characterized by collaborations with various artists such as [[Tinie Tempah]], [[Rich the Kid]] and [[Quavo]]; the album debuted at the top of the [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]] Album Ranking.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fimi.it/classifiche#/category:album/id:2620|title=FIMI - Classifiche - FIMI|website=fimi.it|language=it|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> At the same time, all 11 tracks have conquered the top twelve positions of Top Single (with the sole exception of [[Ed Sheeran]]'s Perfect single, in sixth place).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2018/01/26/sfera-ebbasta-monopolizza-hit-parade_kP9MhuHslnfemlEsHOl6LK.html|title=Sfera Ebbasta monopolizza la hit parade|website=www.adnkronos.com|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> Also, thanks to the success of his album, the rapper became the first Italian artist to position himself among the first hundred of the world ranking compiled by Spotify.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn 13 March 2018 the rapper, along with Charlie Charles, announced the establishment of the record label Billion Headz Music Group,<ref name=\":1\" /> while on 4 May the unpublished single ''Peace & Love'' was released, which also involved the rapper Ghali.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/spettacolo/sfera-ghali-e-charlie-charles-la-nuova-onda-della-trap-all-insegna-di-peace-e-love-_3138026-201802a.shtml|title=Sfera, Ghali e Charlie Charles: la nuova onda della trap all'insegna di \"Peace & Love\" - Tgcom24|work=Tgcom24|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 December 2018 the re-edition of ''Rockstar'', subtitled ''Popstar Edition'', is published, including a second disc containing some remixes and the unreleased tracks ''Popstar'', ''Uh Ah Hey'' and ''Happy Birthday'' (the latter extracted as a single).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sorrisi.com/musica/dischi-in-uscita/sfera-ebbasta-esce-rockstar-pop-star-edition-ecco-cosa-ce-dentro/|title=Sfera Ebbasta, esce \"Rockstar - Pop Star Edition\": ecco cosa c'\u00e8 dentro|date=2018-12-06|website=TV Sorrisi e Canzoni|language=it-IT|access-date=2018-12-08}}</ref>\n\nOn the night of 7 to 8 December 2018, Sfera Ebbasta was due to perform in a nightclub in [[Corinaldo]], near Ancona; during the wait for his appearance, at around 1am, a [[Corinaldo stampede|panic induced stampede]] caused six deaths and dozens of injuries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-46492222|title=Six dead in Italy nightclub stampede|date=2018-12-08|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-12-09|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/six-people-killed-in-nightclub-stampede-in-italy-1.3725008|title=Six people killed in nightclub stampede in Italy|website=The Irish Times|language=en|access-date=2018-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/12/08/italy-nightclub-stampede-corinaldo-rap-concert-sfera-ebbasta/2248972002/|title=6 dead, including 5 young teens, in stampede at overcrowded nightclub on Italy's coast|website=USA TODAY|language=en|access-date=2018-12-09}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with chart positions and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|ITA]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://italiancharts.com/search.asp?search=Sfera+Ebbasta&cat=a|title=Sfera Ebbasta discography|website=italiancharts.com|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(WA)]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Sfera+Ebbasta|title=Discographie Sfera Ebbasta |website=Ultratop.be|accessdate=28 July 2018|language=French}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Sfera+Ebbasta|website=Hitparade.ch|accessdate=28 July 2018|title=Discographie Sfera Ebbasta}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|